  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agri-Enterprise in Sunflower, Soya bean, SIm sim and Sorgham for Small Scale Farmers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project works to enable communities in Northern Uganda to establish small scale sustainable commercial farming businesses to generate incomes for families supporting orphans. The project establishes new Farmer Co-operatives, and supports them with agricultural, business, financial and land-rights awareness training. It also works with whole communities to empower women to achieve equal rights and a voice. It does this by training &#x2018;Community Land Advocacy agents&#x2019;, who improve understanding and respect for land rights, with a focus on wider gender and community relations.</narrative>
  </description>
